rComments: Content is very interesting but not a fan of his lecture style; came off a bit narrow-minded in the sense that he expects students to believe and agree with his opinions. Right from the first lecture, gave the vibe that he didn't care about students. Op-ed paper was graded pretty hard and dropped my mark, exams are fair.

Interesting content, makes it engaging explains concepts well and is enthusiastic about the course content the paper component was a great break from the usual formal paper writing and I enjoyed it. Definitely recommend him If you do readings and study lectures, you'll do well in the course

The prof is smart and explains concept well. However, his exams and reports are unfairly hard. He also has a reputation for not really caring about students. I and my friends have emailed him regarding course work and opportunities and did not even receive a reply. He prefers to do his work and you to leave him alone.

so many readings and makes you purchase and read a book that contradicts lecture -- useless. The course should be named after him instead of Psych of Self-control. spends at least 50% of the time talking about his view on things like a so-called "lit. crisis". he goes over this more than the actual course material. very dry course, talks fast

I regret taking this class b/c his exams are so hard & his lecturing style is all over the place. It's really hard to organize what he says & figure out what you ACTUALLY need to know for the exam. Also, way too many readings. He could have made the course lecture based because a lot of the readings were useless b/c he kept contradicting them.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Love this prof!Inzlicht really makes it easy to pay attention to the full 2 hours of the class. The material is interesting and he explains it so that is easy to understand. Gives lots of opportunity for students to well through bonus points and class engagement, and explains topics and assignments with great detail. Definitely recommend prof/class

By far my favourite Prof, the lecture is very clear and well-connected to the textbook. He gives 2 bonus points for students who attend class with iclicker (more than 50%) or students who write the bonus reaction paper which is free mark. I got 91 with the bonus 2 points and I'm not an A-level student.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Very dull and analytical book which the prof wrote , dislike it

He is very very clear in his explanations! I advise you to study the study questions from lectures because they help you study and see the types of questions you should expect on the exams. The exams include a lot of readings and lecture material (pretty equally) If you are short for time I suggest you study experiments and definitions from both
teacherRatingTags: ['Respected', 'Get ready to read', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Prof. Inzlicht's lectures are some of the most engaging ever! The material is really interesting as well - make sure to attend class and write down notes on the stuff he adds to his slides. There is a lot of reading though, and the main textbook is kinda dry. Make sure to read both + take notes (he tests lecture content as well) to do well.

Amazing professor! Honestly, I signed up for the course because there weren't that many psych courses being offered in the summer. No regret whatsoever, his lectures are VERY interesting and helpful in everyday life. Exams are fair, but I found them to be trickier than most of the other psych exams.

Clear, detailed explanations of the concepts taught in lectures. His exams are half lecture and half textbook which I enjoy very much. Very fair professor. Very knowledgeable. Would love to take another course with him.

Pretty easy class. Just study the lecture notes and all of the assigned readings. The final is harder just because he assigns more readings to do (his own book plus the course textbook). The questions themselves are straightforward, no tricks. He also has 2% bonus available via iclicker or by bonus paper (if you take it with weboption).

He's a great professor, really passionate about what he teaches.  his lectures are interactive and there's an option for extra credit. I'd definitely take another course with him.  exams aren't easy, but aren't super hard either.  make sure you read the books as well.

Dr. Inzlicht is very knowledgeable, and he explains the lecture content very clearly, and makes the course enjoyable and interactive.  However, his exam questions are too particular.  He's not easy, but a good instructor.
Exams are very fair. Just read the textbooks and study his lecture slides. Glad that this course have online lec cuz the prof speaks too fast.
Amazing, amazing prof.  Really clear in his instruction, really informative, keeps lectures interesting.  Exams are fair, option for extra credit.  Read textbook and watch lectures.  Amazing course
hes awesome

He is such a great prof. Honestly I didn't think this was going to be such a great course. He is really clear and good at explaining the lectures. Exams are not extremely hard not to trick you or anything but you must study lec notes and text book, really fair exam. His sample questions are great!

I didn't expect much out of this course but it turned out to be a roller coaster ride in a very good way. Prof Inzlicht is very passionate about the subject, he covers alot in class, provides great examples, his lectures are well organized. His exams are not easy, but they really test your understanding of the material. highly recommend this course

Really enjoyed hid class!! My lectures where online and it was a very interesting and a enjoyable course. He is nice and allows you to earn an extra 2% without much effort. His exams were fair and was not out to get you...a MUST take here at UTSC, even if your not a psy major, you won't regret it! Thanks Prof Inzlicht, your a an amazing prof!!!

Professor Inzlicht is one of the best lecturers I've ever had. He was clearly meant to teach. He is easy to follow, expectations are clear, and tests are fair and reflect what is taught in class. I highly recommend this course!

I really enjoyed Prof. Michael's class because he explains stuff in a very good way. But the thing that I don't like about him is that he kind of speaks really fast (but thankGod there were online lectures available so I could go back if I missed any important point) and other bad thing is that he doesn't answer e-mails. other than that, he is cool
His class was very enjoyable and the exams were very fair.

He's awful! He's so full of himself and "so busy" and so "inflexible". He stated that if we wanted to get our papers re-graded he would mark them and our grade would go down, and if the grade stayed the same, we would lose 5% for making him mark it again! Doesn't he understand that that's his job? It's not my fault your "so busy"...horrible!!!!!!!!

An amazing prof and course. I think this course should be made mandatory for psy majors. He is really good at explaining the material and seems to care whether you understand and learn in his class. His exams are fair, and he is very helpful. His lectures notes are very helpful and good. Doesn't hurt that he is also funny. Very valuable course.

One of the best profs I have ever come across. He deserves a lot of respect. He makes the course fun, even though it was about prejudice, a not so popular topic. Very fair exams--little wonder since he values fairness, and his life's work is indirectly about fairness. Good job! Other profs should follow his teaching style.
Does interesting stuff, like getting an instructor to lead meditation. Cool! I think this is going to be a good class.
Really tries to get students participating. He's very enthusiastic and approachable. Good job!
Diff course but manageable if try hard.

I think Prof. Inzlicht made some very good improvements since the time he came, till now. He posts up all his slides, always very clear, and if something needs to be repeated (especially from that blonde haired girl in the front), He's always helpful. Plus the exams were good too, as long as you study well, you'll do well. great job!

He wastes a lot of time with class discussion, half of which you can't hear because he doesn't repeat the question or comment that was said for the whole class to hear. He doesn't like to reply to emails, he goes too fast to take notes, and doesn't post lecture notes online until after the class (he's "too busy").  Very obvious he's a new prof.

Doesn't seem like a easy prof. Right now taking this course seems to be a drag. He doesn't like responding to emails which make him worse. Plus, goes on and on with experiments and results. One of the most boring courses in psychology. The exam is mainly multiple choice (tough and tricky questions..as he mentioned). Overall, not a good experience.

He's a self-important, pre-occupied **** who can't get his act together in time to post his lecture slides before class. He wastes time with pointless class discussion (he actually told a 250 person class to break up into little groups for twenty minutes and decide how to test for stereotypes, and then spent another fifteen taking up answers)
Taking the course right now. He's a fast talker, take quick notes. As the for tests, it's practically all multiple choice.
